> Confirmed — pointer-move has no (when (not= @mode :idle) ...) guard at the top, so the 
:idle default branch runs on every hover. The (when (and @drag-moved? ...) check prevents 
drawing, but drag-moved? is computed from start-cx/start-cy which are 0 initially — so any 
mouse movement from (0,0) could exceed 4px and set drag-moved? to true even without a pointer
-down.

Two fixes: guard the entire pointer-move body with a "pointer is captured" check, and clear 
drag-ghost on mount.
