> Also set mode to :pending on pointer-down (not :idle) so the move guard works, and 
transition to :idle only after pointer-up. Actually simpler — the pointer-down already sets 
mode to :idle and the timer sets it to :deck-drag. The move guard (not= @mode :idle) blocks 
hover. But during a real drag, mode starts as :idle until either the timer fires (:deck-drag)
or movement triggers the draw (:card-drag). So the guard blocks the draw branch too.

